summary: This is a Victim Services Division documentation of services provided to an unnamed victim in an FBI case, covering the period from January 1, 2000, to August 14, 2020. The record shows various types of follow-up contacts and referrals made, with a note emphasizing that the document is discoverable and should not contain mental health information or personal opinions.

events.title: Victim Services Record Download
events.description: A Victim Services Division record documenting services provided to a victim was downloaded, covering services from January 1, 2000, to August 14, 2020.

keyFacts: The document is a Victim Services Division record of services provided to a victim in an FBI case.
Services were provided over a 20-year period from January 1, 2000, to August 14, 2020.
The record includes various service types: Crisis Intervention, Follow-Up Contacts (in person, phone, text), Initial Contact Text, Other, and Resource/Referral for Counseling.
A note on the document states it is discoverable and instructs to limit comments to logistical or service referral information, avoiding mental health details or personal opinions.
The victim's name and FBI case number are not disclosed in the provided text.
